---
// src/pages/controls-ios-application.astro
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
const title = "Controls IOS Application";
const publishDate = "April 10, 2025";
---
<Layout title={`${title} - Project`}>
  <main class="container mx-auto px-4 py-16">
    <article class="glass p-12 rounded-3xl max-w-3xl mx-auto">
      <!-- Project Header -->
      <header class="mb-8">
        <h1 class="text-5xl font-bold mb-2">{title}</h1>
        <p class="text-gray-200 text-lg">Published on {publishDate}</p>
      </header>

      <!-- Project Content -->
      <section class="prose max-w-none text-gray-200">
        <p>
          The PID Controls Simulator is a personal project created to experiment with Apple's Swift language, PID control implementation, and functional UI design.
        </p>
        <p>
          The iOS application features a simulator with a desired setpoint of 50 along with six critical variables: Kp, Ki, Kd, Current Value, Signal, and Noise. The current value is graphically plotted on a custom bitmap that automatically scales without going out of bounds.
        </p>
        <p>
          The control signal is computed with:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Proportional:</strong> Kp * current error</li>
          <li><strong>Integral:</strong> Ki * cumulative error</li>
          <li><strong>Derivative:</strong> Kd * (difference in error over time)</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          The app also features noise and nudge controls to simulate disturbances and adjust the value in real time.
        </p>

        <!-- Embedded YouTube Video -->
        <div class="video-container my-8">
          <iframe 
            width="360" 
            height="415" 
            src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/wM4RfHS1H-I" 
            title="YouTube video player" 
            frameborder="0" 
            allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture" 
            allowfullscreen 
            class="rounded-2xl w-full">
          </iframe>
        </div>
        
      </section>
    </article>
  </main>
</Layout>
